  "title": "Horticulturist / Arborist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description/ Responsibility</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Project Management Duties</li>\n  <li>Monitor site operation and supervises ground workers and assist maintenance crew in horticultural tasks</li>\n  <li>Plan the work programme and continually assess, meeting with Client's representatives or appointed Consultant, review and improve on performance including the conduct of risk assessment and management</li>\n  <li>Conduct regular inspection to make sure to meet the Service Level Agreement</li>\n  <li>Handle the administration of all works in the Contract including receiving and responding to the Client/ his representatives or appointed Consultant's directions issued</li>\n  <li>Liaise with clients on enquiries, feedbacks and complaints</li>\n  <li>Attend joint site inspect with the Client/ his representatives or appointed Consultant and attend to defects and shortcomings highlighted during such inspection within given deadline</li>\n  <li>Any other roles assigned by managers/director</li>\n  <li>Able to work under pressure and work beyond normal working hours and on weekends/public holidays if required</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirement</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Horticulture/ Landscape Management or WSQ Advanced Certificate in Landscape Supervision or WSQ Diploma in Landscape Management (Any Landscape Related Course)</li>\n  <li>Arborist certification from International Society of Arboriculture (ISA) or equivalent</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of relevant experience in Landscape Industry</li>\n  <li>Able to work outdoor and sun loving personnel</li>\n  <li>Possess valid Class 2B/ Class 3 and above will be a bonus</li>\n</ul>",
